        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hello,\n\nWith Zend 1.7.3, when I execute a sql query on a table which has a date field and a text field then the returned date is corrupted. When I change the text field to a varchar field, it works fine.\nIf I copy Zend_Db_Statement_Mysqli.php from Zend 1.5.0 to Zend 1.7.3 then it works fine.\n\nHere is a test scenario:\nCreate the database named \"space\" with a single table in it:\n{code:sql}\nCREATE TABLE `test_table` (\n  `id` int(7) NOT NULL auto_increment,\n  `login` varchar(20) NOT NULL default '',\n  `birthdate` date default NULL,\n  `abc` text NOT NULL,\n  PRIMARY KEY  (`id`)\n) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1 AUTO_INCREMENT=2 ;\nINSERT INTO `test_table` VALUES(1, 'atm', '2009-01-06', '');\n{code}\nWith this small piece of code:\n{code:none}\n<?\nrequire_once '\/var\/www\/zend\/library\/Zend\/Loader.php';\nZend_Loader::registerAutoload();\n\n      $params = array('host'=>'localhost', 'username'=>'test', 'password'=>'test, 'dbname'=>'space');\n      $db = Zend_Db::factory('Mysqli', $params);\n\n      $select = $db->select()->from('test_table')->where('login=?', 'atm');\n      $stmt = $db->query($select);\n      $result = $stmt->fetchAll();\n      Zend_Debug::dump($result);\n?>\n{code}\n\nWe can see that the \"birthdate\" field is corrupted. The output of the php code is:\n{code:none}\narray(1) {\n  [0] => array(4) {\n    [\"id\"] => int(1)\n    [\"login\"] => string(3) \"atm\"\n    [\"birthdate\"] => string(10) \"2-@n\"\n    [\"abc\"] => string(0) \"\"\n  }\n}\n\nzend_mm_heap corrupted\n{code}\n\nHere is my PHP and MySQL versions:\nPHP 5.2.3 (cli) (built: Dec  5 2007 17:14:53)\nCopyright (c) 1997-2007 The PHP Group\nZend Engine v2.2.0, Copyright (c) 1998-2007 Zend Technologies\n\nmysql  Ver 14.7 Distrib 4.1.7, for pc-linux (i686)\nCopyright (C) 2002 MySQL AB\n\nI have also tested with PHP 5.2.8 and I get the same behavior.\n\nMaybe I have done something wrong ? Can you please give us your opinion ?\n\nThanks,\nAnh Tuan."
        },
