                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33559",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jimbojsb",
                        "name": "jimbojsb",
                        "displayName": "Josh Butts",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Tested with ZF Trunk, PHP 5.2.3 and Mysql 4.1 in a 32 bit Linux VM and could not reproduce this.  The fact that a zend_mm_heap_corrupted is reported is indicative of a segmentation fault or similar issue that would be near-impossible to reproduce from system to system unless the issue is at the language level rather than the framework level.  The fact that changing from a text to a varchar solved the problem at that point further illustrates the point, as the difference there at the driver level could easily push it in or out of segfault range.  A quick scan of of the PHP bug tracker didn't reveal anything relevant or related.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jimbojsb",
                        "name": "jimbojsb",
                        "displayName": "Josh Butts",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-17T19:12:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-17T19:12:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
